        Nicknamed the Bay State, Massachusetts, located on the eastern coast, stretches approximately 1,500 miles down the Atlantic coastline, and features over 1,000 ponds, lakes, and rivers spread throughout. Originally part of the thirteen colonies, Massachusetts is surrounded by six New England states and is home to over 7 million people. Due to its location, Massachusetts stays relatively cold throughout the year, with significant snowfall during the winter and summer temperatures in the 70-degree Fahrenheit range. (Tager, 2025)
